e in English on the last line of the recipient\u2019s address Online Shipping Calculator.3.\n\n## Relevant Context 3\n\u2026\nDiscover what's next\nhow to send a \npostcard to USPS\nhow to mail a letter \nto USPS\nhow to send a \npostcard address\n\nat eval (eval at evaluate (:290:30), <anonymous>:1:1)\n    at eval (<anonymous>)\n    at UtilityScript.evaluate (<anonymous>:290:30)\n    at UtilityScript.<anonymous> (<anonymous>:1:44)\n\n## Relevant Context 4\nAdd Postage\nFor a standard 1 oz letter, use a First-Class Mail Forever\u00ae stamp ($0.78 in 2026) USPS.com.If your letter exceeds 1 oz or uses a large envelope, calculate additional postage using USPS\u2019s online postage calculator Online Shipping Calculator.Read all\nUSPS.com\nhttps://www.usps.com \u203a ship \u203a letters.htm\nHow to Send a Letter or Postcard | USPSJun 8, 2021 \u00b7 USPS shows you how to send a letter or postcard in the U.S., from choosing an envelope, writing the address, buying and applying stamps, and finding a drop-off location. Total Time: 2 mins\nGround AdvantageUSPS Ground Advantage\u2122 service is an affordable and reliable way to send packages inside the U.S. expected in 2\u20135 business days for items up to 70 lbs.\n"